[{"id":"VR001466","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a laser shooting  light towards a sensor. The laser light moves horizontally and to the right and is represented by a line with several arrowheads pointing to the right. The light passes through the centers of two filters that are labeled Filter 1 and Filter 2 before hitting the sensor.  At the center points of both Filter 1 and Filter 2, dashed vertical lines move upward and are labeled 0 degrees.\" height=\"193\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR001466.g01.png\" width=\"450\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a wave in the first quadrant of a coordinate plane. The horizontal axis is labeled “Angle of Filter 2, in degrees,” and the values 0 through 400, in increments of 100, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Relative Intensity,” and is 10 units high. Note that all values are approximate. The wave begins at 0 degrees and 3 units up the vertical axis, and ends at 360 degrees and 2.5 units up the vertical axis. The wave reaches a maximum at the following 4 points. A wave peak at 60 degrees and 10 units up the vertical axis. A wave trough at 150 degrees and 0 units up the vertical axis. A wave peak at 240 degrees and 10 units up the vertical axis. A wave trough at 330 degrees and 0 units up the vertical axis.\" height=\"284\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR001466.g03.png\" width=\"400\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A laser is directed toward a pair of identical linear polarizing filters with unknown orientation. The intensity of laser light that passes through both filters is measured by a sensor. In order for the orientation of the filters to be determined, filter 2 is rotated through <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"360 degrees\"><math alttext=\"360 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>360</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span> from its initial orientation. The graph plots the resulting intensity data as a function of the angle of rotation. Which of the following explains how to determine the orientation of filter 1 ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR001466_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The filters each spin the wave by the same amount, and maximum intensity is measured when filter 2 is rotated <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"60 degrees\"><math alttext=\"60 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>60</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span>, so filter 1 must be oriented <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"30 degrees\"><math alttext=\"30 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>30</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span> from vertical.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Minimum intensity occurs when the polarizers are perpendicular to one another, and minimum intensity is measured when filter 2 is rotated <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"150 degrees\"><math alttext=\"150 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>150</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span>, so filter 1 must be oriented <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"60 degrees\"><math alttext=\"60 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>60</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span> from vertical.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Maximum intensity occurs when the polarizers are parallel to one another, and maximum intensity is measured when filter 2 is rotated <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"60 degrees\"><math alttext=\"60 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>60</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span>, so filter 1 must be oriented <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"120 degrees\"><math alttext=\"120 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>120</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span> from vertical.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The measured light intensity goes through two complete cycles as filter 2 is rotated through <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"360 degrees\"><math alttext=\"360 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>360</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span>, so filter 1 must be oriented <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"180 degrees\"><math alttext=\"180 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>180</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span> from vertical.</p>"],"answer":1}]